



In Council Nov. 9. 1779.



The board are of opinion that Colo. Le Maires expences of 15,545 livres 14 sous be paid in current money at the exchange of 20 for 1. and that 2000 be allowed him for his expences from Boston to this day.
Th: Jefferson
In Council Nov. 12. 1779
On further consideration the board thinks Mr. Le Maire shoud be allowed 27. livres a day for 430 days to be paid in currency at a rate not exceeding twenty five for one.

Th: Jefferson

